The paper deals with the design of a spectral method for signal recovery, specifically for phase retrieval. This involves optimization in a weighted $L^2$ function space, which suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses numerical simulations, which could fall under numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper mentions applications to computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SI).
